## 8. Database Encryption Implementation

### Prisma Schema with Encrypted Fields

```prisma
model User {
  id            String   @id @default(uuid())
  phone_enc     Bytes    // AES-256-GCM encrypted
  phone_hash    String   @unique // SHA-256 hash for lookup
  email_enc     Bytes?   // AES-256-GCM encrypted
  email_hash    String?  @unique
  password_hash String   // bcrypt
  role          UserRole
  is_active     Boolean  @default(true)
  created_at    DateTime @default(now())
  updated_at    DateTime @updatedAt
}

model Patient {
  id              String  @id @default(uuid())
  user_id         String  @unique
  first_name_enc  Bytes   // encrypted
  last_name_enc   Bytes   // encrypted
  dob_enc         Bytes   // encrypted
  allergies_enc   Bytes?  // encrypted (sensitive medical data)
  medical_notes_enc Bytes? // encrypted (sensitive medical data)
}
```

